Two separate shack blazes broke out in the same informal settlement in Philippi in the space of a few hours early of Sunday morning. CAPE TOWN - A series of fires over the weekend have claimed three lives. Two separate shack blazes broke out in the same informal settlement in Philippi in the space of a few hours early of Sunday morning. A boy and a man died. On Sunday, another fire erupted in the very same area. In Kraaifontein a man died in a shack fire.